    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Rug motifs that are cuff-shaped, in which each cuff appears as a triangle with a narrow link between the two hypotaneuses. In some cases, the "cuff" is surrounded by a diamond, which may be stepped.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
